{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17647668","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17647668"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:46:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:46:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18256"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18256","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18256"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.04,0.74,0.04,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10970"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80168"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10970","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10970"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18256"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65445"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7456"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25488"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25489"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80168","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80168"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe sartorius muscle is a long, ribbon-like muscle that runs obliquely across the anterior thigh.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the function of the sartorius muscle?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Flexion and medial rotation of the hip","Extension and lateral rotation of the hip","Flexion, abduction, and lateral rotation of the hip","Extension and abduction of the hip","Adduction and medial rotation of the hip"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esartorius muscle\u003C/strong\u003E is the longest muscle in the human body and is involved in multiple actions at the hip and knee joints. It originates from the anterior superior iliac spine and inserts into the medial aspect of the proximal tibia. The primary functions of the sartorius include \u003Cem\u003Eflexion, abduction, and lateral rotation of the hip\u003C/em\u003E, as well as flexion of the knee joint.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlexion and medial rotation of the hip\u003C/strong\u003E are not actions performed by the sartorius. Medial rotation is typically associated with muscles like the gluteus medius and minimus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtension and lateral rotation of the hip\u003C/strong\u003E are actions associated with muscles such as the gluteus maximus, not the sartorius.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdduction and medial rotation of the hip\u003C/strong\u003E are not functions of the sartorius. Adduction is primarily performed by the adductor group of muscles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtension and abduction of the hip\u003C/strong\u003E are not actions of the sartorius. Extension is primarily performed by the gluteus maximus and hamstrings.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The sartorius muscle is involved in flexion, abduction, and lateral rotation of the hip joint.","The sartorius also assists in flexion of the knee joint."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2018). Textbook of Orthopaedics, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Singh, V. (2018). Textbook of Anatomy Abdomen and Lower Limb; Volume II (Vol. 2). Elsevier Health Sciences","Cantrell AJ, Imonugo O, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Leg Bones. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537024/","Raftery A. General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System. Ann R Coll Surg Engl. 2006 Jul;88(4):425. doi: 10.1308/003588406X114802d. PMCID: PMC1964629","Chaudhry SR, Nahian A, Chaudhry K. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis, Pelvis. [Updated 2023 Jul 25]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482258/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65445"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18256"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65445","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65445"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T22:42:11+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T22:43:07+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10970"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80168"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":